    <section>
        <h1>Our <span>Mission</span></h1>
        <p>This system was designed to bridge the gap between environmental data and public safety. By utilizing clean, modern code, we ensure that critical information is delivered fast and clearly.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Who We Are & <span>What We Do</span></h2>
        <p>We are <strong>Team DEWS</strong>. We recognize that for decades, our global approach to drought has been entirely reactive—a "silent catastrophe" where agricultural and economic devastation is already underway by the time a drought is officially declared.</p>
        <p>To shift agriculture from reactive damage control to proactive resilience, we built <strong>DEWS: the Drought Early Warning System</strong>. Our machine learning architecture looks far beyond standard meteorological models. By ingesting massive, disparate datasets—decades of historical climate records, real-time satellite imagery, and localized soil moisture telemetry—DEWS identifies complex, hidden climate patterns that human analysts simply cannot see.</p>
        <p>The result is a multi-horizon predictive engine that generates highly accurate, localized drought probability forecasts for one, three, and nine months into the future. We are dedicated to providing precision agriculture powered by predictive AI, giving farmers the one resource they have never had: <em>time</em>.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>How to Use <span>DEWS</span></h2>
        <p>We built the DEWS platform to be universally accessible, from large-scale agricultural corporations to small family farms. An AI model is only as valuable as its adoption, so we designed our interface to be seamless:</p>
        <ul>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>1. Input Your Location:</strong> Navigate to our visualizer dashboard and select your specific geographic area.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>2. Review the Forecast:</strong> The system will process the data and display the localized drought probability forecast horizons.</li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 10px;"><strong>3. Apply Actionable Intelligence:</strong> DEWS doesn't just say when a drought is coming; it tells you what to do about it. The system synthesizes the prediction with local crop data to prescribe the best course of action—such as optimizing irrigation schedules, recommending drought-resistant seed variants, or altering harvest timelines.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>
